<br>
Some people will _never_ agree with you. <br>
<br>
As for being ignored. Sometimes I find it pleasurable to be ignored by certain people. It saves me time and energy I'd rather expend elsewhere. Some people I have no further use for. They've been found lacking, to borrow a phrase from the Execution trials, and whatever they do to enforce a sentence of silence vis-a-vis me is a great  bonus <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
For example, one of Saalron's old tricks was to aggrieve someone and then turn around and do something good for potential allies of the aggrieved person. I've witnessed guild situations where person A sided with a miscreant just because the person in question &quot;raided alot&quot; or &quot;helped with alot of guild stuff.&quot; The facts of the situation itself were MEANINGLESS in all reality. <br>
<br>
So in that situation, I would adore being ignored by such an idiot who decided to side with the miscreant. Such a person has done me a wonderous favor by such Saalronesquse behavior. Having no further communication with that person is something I like. <br>
<br>
So ignoring someone is not always a &quot;punishment&quot;.... sometimes it's a gift that keeps on giving <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rangergoldeneyes>RangerGoldeneyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 954<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/9/02 3:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1809.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.texasranger.org/Fake_Badges/Final/Badgerepl(1).jpg height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Use him like the tool he is</span><hr size=1> ya, i have to agree with Pry, i kind of miss Bled and Baerfag now that we don't have them to kick around anymore <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=1809.topic&start=21&stop=29>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1809.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1809.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1809.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1809.t